==German==
===Etymology===
Old High German ''[[ūf]]'', originally *''ūp''
===Preposition===
'''auf'''
#[[on]] -- es liegt ''auf dem'' Tisch (it is on the table) dat
#[[onto]] -- stell es ''auf den'' Tisch (place it on the table) acc

''Note:'' The preposition "an" is used with accusative case if the verb shows movement from one place to another, whereas it is used with dative case if the verb shows location.

===Interjection===
'''auf!'''
#[[Carry on]]!
#[[have a go]]!

